pullRequest.body:
`Functor.IsEquivalence` is now the combination of `F.Full`, `F.Faithful` and `F.EssSurj`. That such a functor is an equivalence (i.e. there is a quasi-inverse, etc.) is now contained in the definition `F.asEquivalence`. This refactor is to avoid any diamond in the `IsEquivalence` instances (and also for `IsLeftAdjoint` and `IsRightAdjoint` which are also made `Props`). If data is important, one should use `Equivalence` or `Adjunction` instead. This refactor also avoids some duplication of code between the structures `Equivalence` and the former `IsEquivalence`.

`IsLeftAdjoint` and `IsRightAdjoint` are moved to the `Functor` namespace. The namespaces have also been fixed in the file `CategoryTheory.Adjunction.FullyFaithful`. Proofs have been tidied in `CategoryTheory.Monoidal.NaturalTransformation`.

Definitions which relied on `IsLeft/RightAdjoint` have been modified in order to contain the data of an adjunction (e.g. `Reflective`, `MonadicRightAdjoint`, etc.).

---

The most relevant changes are in `CategoryTheory.Equivalence`. Then, most of the fixes are straightforward. Those that are not are mostly in files related to monoidal categories.

Here are the [benchmark results](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/run-detail/857ebdf0-ac6a-402e-a6f3-e4a2c83f90dc) for commit 020de8a56dc89d828e10c23cbaeab244ce77b1f0.
There were [significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/c7e70f30-e69b-4eef-8d2b-d04b27dee27d/to/857ebdf0-ac6a-402e-a6f3-e4a2c83f90dc) against commit 8d0c6e6f821392660468fdce7c5463740d7988be:
```diff
  Benchmark                                              Metric         Change
  ============================================================================
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Localization.Predicate         instructions   -51.7%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monad.Monadicity               instructions   -32.3%
- ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monoidal.OfHasFiniteProducts   instructions   113.7%
```

> ```diff
> - ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monoidal.OfHasFiniteProducts   instructions   113.7%
> ```

Note: this is because I have added a new definition `Functor.toMonoidalFunctorOfHasFiniteProducts` which transforms a functor commuting with finite products to a monoidal functor for the monoidal structure given by finite products. I introduced this in order to get a cleaner definition of `cartesianClosedOfEquiv` at https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/12462/files#diff-0b936081067ad5cf5b6cba85a5895474e77d1d3fa27b3a502700ed5f230ae9e2R415-R416

We probably want something like (needs `import Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Adjunction.Opposites`):

```lean
noncomputable def leftAdjointCongr {F G : D ⥤ C} (i : F ≅ G) [F.IsRightAdjoint] :
    haveI := isRightAdjoint_of_iso i
    leftAdjoint F ≅ leftAdjoint G :=
  haveI := isRightAdjoint_of_iso i
  ((Adjunction.ofIsRightAdjoint F).ofNatIsoRight i).leftAdjointUniq (Adjunction.ofIsRightAdjoint G)
```

(and similarly for right adjoints) since we're losing the defeq of `rightAdjointOfNatIso` and its dual. 

Otherwise I think it's a really good change to make these classes `Prop`-valued and it's fine if this is added in a followup PR if we want to keep the refactor separate.

Thanks very much for having a look at this PR!

> We probably want something like (needs `import Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Adjunction.Opposites`):
> 
> ```lean
> noncomputable def leftAdjointCongr {F G : D ⥤ C} (i : F ≅ G) [F.IsRightAdjoint] :
>     haveI := isRightAdjoint_of_iso i
>     leftAdjoint F ≅ leftAdjoint G :=
> ```

I do not think we want this exact definition because this isomorphism is not unique (if `F` has automorphisms)!

What we could do is generalize the definitions which are used in `leftAdjointUniq`: if `G ⊣ F` and `G' ⊣ F'` are adjunctions, then there are bijections `(G ⟶ G') ≃ (F' ⟶ F)` and `(G ≅ G') ≃ (F' ≅ F)`.

> What we could do is generalize the definitions which are used in `leftAdjointUniq`: if `G ⊣ F` and `G' ⊣ F'` are adjunctions, then there are bijections `(G ⟶ G') ≃ (F' ⟶ F)` and `(G ≅ G') ≃ (F' ≅ F)`.

I'm working on this in a separate PR
#12625 is the refactor of `leftAdjointUniq`

Thanks!
